olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet mixed sesame seeds
2 clove garlic
1 cucumber
1 tbs honey
1 tbs water
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Asian Slaw Mix
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Japanese Dressing
packet coriander

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries and mixed sesame seeds on a lined oven tray. Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with olive oil.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• While the fries are baking, finely chop garlic. Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons.
• In a small bowl, combine the soy sauce, honey and the water. Set aside.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the sauces!

• In a large bowl, combine pork mince, ginger paste, garlic, fine breadcrumbs and the egg,
then season with salt and pepper.
• Using damp hands, form heaped spoonfuls of pork mixture into meatballs, then flatten to make 2cm-thick rissoles (3-4 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook rissoles until
browned all over and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side.
• Add the honey-soy glaze and cook, tossing rissoles to coat, until slightly reduced, 1 minute. Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

• Divide honey-soy pork rissoles and sesame fries between plates.
• Serve with Japanese cucumber slaw.
• Tear over coriander (see ingredients) to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the herbs!

• Divide honey-soy pork rissoles and sesame fries between plates. Serve with Japanese cucumber
slaw.
• Tear over coriander (see ingredients) to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the herbs!